This paper deals with the runtime analysis of an estimation-of-distribution algorithm (EDA) on a multimodal problem, specifically the compact genetic algorithm (cGA) on the $n$-dimensional jump function. This problem is related to optimization and search algorithms, which are typically studied in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The paper also involves mathematical analysis and probability theory, which are relevant to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. Additionally, the use of EDAs and evolutionary algorithms falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
